latestPosts.caption:
DIY heatless fireplace that looks like the real thing!

So a couple of things that I feel I should tell you: 

The sketch is very detailed. But the mouldings are not included. We used a mix of 3" and 2" moulding. Ask in the comments section any info or If you want one made, let us know. We make it for a living. 😂 

The humidifier is from Amazon. You'll get plenty of them. 

The buttery cream is a mix of annie sloan country grey + Asian paints sweet corn + Asian paints blossom tint in the ratio 4: 1: 10

We used an oil based primer here because it's wood. Wood + water based primer = possibility of mould. 

We used the tv socket to power the humidifier - we did a small hole on the back of the hearth area to run the usb wire.

Please do not chop a tree because you need wood for display. Look for fallen trees or trees that are struck by lightning. Chop them. Don't be that guy. 

I'm looking at adding a crackling sound machine so I'll update on that! 

For now, may your day be hyggeligt

#apartmentgarden #tips How to have abundant rosemary in your kitchen garden!
.
Rosemary hates too much water. It's a Mediterranean, drought tolerant so it'll be fine if you water every day (if temps are over 35) and every alternate day (if temps are below 29)
.
Mist the plants everyday if you stay in a dusty area. Like I do. 
.
Periodically, add a good nitrogen fertilizer: I have started adding muzus hair. Haha. Or NPK: 10:0:0.
.
Add little compost once a month. 
.
4 to 6 hours of sunlight.
.
Harvest regularly

Sunroom #makeover part 2! 

Adding veneer to the table top, smoothing the edges, waxing it and then finally painting. Honestly I tried colors for the leg but in the larger scheme of things it wasn't looking very good.

Here's a bit of a #homedecor advice. 

There is the look of an individual piece and then there is how it'll look in the scheme of your home. Always consider that, unless you have fallen in love with a piece and you just want that. In that case of course, go right ahead. Build the rest around it. But do consider the rest of the home. 

We also added a farmhouse style brass rail on the wall to hold our hats and knick-knacks. 

Step 3 is lighting and finally getting the plant trolley in! Given my pace count another 7 days. 

Everything will be documented in my blog after the 3 parts because it's easier to search.

Okay happy Friday! Yay, weekend aa gaya!

P.s. Sahil is our commander in chief in all DIY projects. If you've been following me for a while, you'd know.

The sun is lingering, the breeze is warm, and the solstice is quietly asking you to notice. It's #summersolstice☀️ the longest day of the year and you absolutely must go to a nature spot. 

Honestly I don't know why you absolutely must but I think it's a great idea 😃

A hush of hue, and a surface that speaks.
Specta’s Pastel Poise collection unveils four quartz stones — delicate yet durable, quietly confident.

Mint Mirage — a breeze of green veined with stillness, casting shade and shimmer in equal measure.

Gulmarg Pink — a bloom of blush and warmth, where peach and ivory veins dance in soft romance.

Lavender Crest — a violet tide, crystalline and cool, glowing with layered light.

Azure Haze — a powder-blue whisper, traced with mist and cloud, lightening every corner it touches.

I absolutely loved putting these moodboards together and I cannot wait to use the gorgeous collection in my projects. Let me know which one is your fav in the comments section!

#SpectaQuartzSurfaces #PastelPoise #DesignWithGrace #StoneStories #QuietLuxury #DecorPoetry #KingOfQuartz

They say designers — like journalists — shouldn’t be biased. But we’re only human, and it’s hard not to have favorites. 

As we wrap up the visual guide and my client begins civil work, I feel a deep, quiet affection for this particular home we’re about to transform. I find myself returning to the final renders, smiling at the thought of how it will all come together — how the space will feel, dressed and ready, and how joyfully it will be lived in.

It’s the kind of fulfilment that lingers.

latestPosts.caption:
A story of time, of tenderness, of scent.

Introducing the @trumatter Signature Soy Wax Candle Collection, a quartet of hand-poured moments drawn from nature’s most evocative corners. We’ve spent countless hours—nose deep in blossoms, wax under fingernails—perfecting these fragrances. And it shows.

Crafted in small batches with 100% pure soy wax, our candles burn clean and slow, soft as cream to the touch, with a scent throw that lingers like memory.

🌿 Country Bouquet
White gardenia, jasmine, magnolia blossom.
Fresh, airy, and deeply floral—like a morning walk through a sunlit garden.

🍾 Summer Fête
Champagne, peony, almond crème.
A sparkle in scent form—joyful, sweet, with just enough indulgence.

🌼 Sonchafa
Creamy magnolia champaca.
Rooted in nostalgia, warm and golden—this is tradition wrapped in petals.

🖤 Art Room
Oud and smoky whiskey.
Moody and refined. Like wet paint, aged books, candlelight on canvas.

We made them slowly. So you could burn them slowly.
Light one. Let your room remember something beautiful.

#TrumatterCandles #CountryInEveryCorner #ScentedSlow #SmallBatchBeauty #SoyWaxCandles

We got south of France to Bhopal! Hopefully landscape the garden with all native plants! 

Not everyday a girl gets to design an entire courtyard and not everyday one gets a client who says french country with as much passion and love as I do. 

And I know that when this is done, the space will outdo the renders. 

Cannot wait!
